  "title": "Work Safety Officer (WSH)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Industry: </strong>Industrial and Technology Industry</p><p><strong>Location: </strong>West area</p><p><strong>Skills:</strong> Workplace Safety and Security</p><p>This vacancy will fill a role in Workplace and Safety focusing on Building and Facilities area. </p><p><strong>Position Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Primary focus on driving, working and facilitating day-to-day EHS initiatives.</li><li>Lead improvement of workplace and safety standards and practices at the workplace.</li><li>Handle reports and activities, conduct regular inspection and training orientation for all staff for proper conduct to maintain work place safety.</li></ul><p><strong>Position Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must be a Workplace Safety & Health Officer registered with Ministry Of Manpower (MOM) and a registered Environmental Control Officer (ECO) with National Environment Agency (NEA).</li><li>Experience and good knowledge of Environment, Workplace Safety & Health Management Systems such as ISO14001 and ISO45001 including and BizSAFE Certification.</li><li>2 years experience as a WSH Officer.</li><li>Flexible with work hours (eg: Public Holidays, Weekends and outside regular work hours).</li><li>Able to write Chinese manuscripts and reports.</li></ul><p>We will look into all candidate profile but will prioritize those closest to the requirement.<br /></p><p>Thank you!<br /></p><p>Joseph Syho</p><p>Reg Number: R1108657</p><p>EA Licence No: 18C9079</p>",
